helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 26.16 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: SERIOUS CONCERNS
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hey Ian,
I wanted to say thank you for your help thus far, not just with trying to get me into the useful part of the digital learning landscape, but also for everything you've done prior to classes starting - you've been extremely informative and prompt with your correspondence and I really do appreciate it. The same cannot be said, however, for the IT Help desk. I know they're probably swamped with tickets given what time of year it is so I completely understand if they aren't as swift with their service as they usually are. Regardless of the pace with which they address tickets, I expect the incident to be fixed once the ticket is closed. This morning I received notice that, for the second time, my login issues should be fixed. This was not the case. I am still experiencing the same invalid login credentials error. To make matters worse, when I tried to log into my MSOE email to write this message to you I was greeted by a separate screen after entering in my login information that read "Something went wrong. We can't get that information right now. Please try again later." The header above that text was a sad faced emoticon - very fitting.
I can only do so much about this problem. If it can be determined that my hardware is somehow incompatible with Blackboard then I'll gladly fling my computer from my apartment window and buy a brand new one. If I have to take time off of work to physically visit somebody in IT during their office hours then I'll do that. I am more than willing to do whatever it takes to make this problem go away but somebody needs to tell me what that is because I couldn't possibly guess my way to a conclusion at this point.
Regarding my academics - I've been in contact with both of my professors who have been very patient and understanding during this kerfuffle. I am still uneasy about falling behind with my work especially considering the warning that was issued to me during orientation about doing exactly that. I would really like to be given some piece of mind that if some nightmare scenario does play out where it takes forever and a day to put this issue to bed that I'll still be able to pursue my degree unscathed by follies of a less-than-perfect digital interface.
I've been attempting to attend graduate school for three years now. The first attempt was partially funded by a scholarship I was receiving through a group affiliated with my then employer. That scholarship was mismanaged and discontinued before I could start and I could not afford the program on my own. A year later at a different university my second attempt was thwarted by my program being discontinued in the state of Wisconsin due to regulatory reasons. This year I was legitimately excited to finally fulfill my goal at a really first-rate institution that would help me learn, network, and advance myself as a person and a professional. I want to make sure this still happens, but as of now I have concerns. Any thoughts or suggestions would be appreciated. Thank you.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: MSOE Tower Internet
helpdesk-ticket.description:
The MSOE tower internet is ridiculous. I know this issue has been discussed already and the tower residence received an email regarding it. However, in that email it said the internet problems started movie-in day and each day around 6:30, both of which are not true. I was here the entire summer and I noticed the internet was lacking from its usual performance, with significantly less people because school was not in session. I figured it may get fixed because school was starting and the internet would become a priority. It is now 1:51 and I am getting ping of over 300 and it is not even close to 6:30.
Did something change with the internet over the summer? Last year, for the entire year, my roommate and I never had a problem.
Thanks,
Alex

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Amanda,
Thanks for your e-mail.
No, it actually is still a problem. However, I did some research on the error message. It looks like it's a problem associated with a graphics driver. The error code is BCCode: 116. Microsoft suggests making sure all updates are installed --
http://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/all/blue-screen-bccode-116/70bda113-799b-4b9d-ae50-ca570136e7f8 -- and I've found other solutions (e.g., new motherboard, Windows re-install, etc.).
Basically, the blue screen occurs when I try to view a YouTube video, so I've avoided doing that for the time being.
Probably the best solution is to re-install Windows. However, I'll probably need to wait until after the academic quarter. If I can bring the laptop over to the Help Desk earlier, I will. In the meantime, I'm backing up my data.
Thanks,
Gary Library

helpdesk-ticket.description: Xbox one can't connect to multiplayer services. It says that it cannot get a Teredo IP Address. Reading up online says that it's because the correct ports for xbox multiplayer might not be open, or it is because IPV6 is causing issues with the way xbox handles that.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Xbox one can't connect to multiplayer services. It says that it cannot get a Teredo IP Address. Reading up online says that it's because the correct ports for xbox multiplayer might not be open, or it is because IPV6 is causing issues with the way xbox handles that.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jonathon,
MSOE does not use NAT at this time. All IP addresses are internet-routable, and are not translated IP addresses. The IP you get when connecting to our network is the one that people outside our network see. You will only have a NAT if you are using a router or switch that provides DHCP other than the DHCP provided by MSOE.
That being said, we are familiar with what XBO considers NAT. The reason you may see errors along the line of "Can't get a Teredo IP address" is indicating that XBO did not get and cannot see an IPv6 network. MSOE blocks all IPv6 traffic as our servers, routers, and firewalls do not have policies in place to manage IPv6 traffic. All IPv6 traffic will revert to IPv4 if it cannot establish a connection. Use of IPv6 or IPv4 will not impact your network experience.
There are some steps you can take if you are using a router or switch between your device and our network. You can forward ports on your router to the IP address of your XBO. This will require giving the XBO a static IP address. You can also place your XBO in the DMZ of the route. This will also require a static IP, but is less effort than setting up port forwarding. This puts your XBO outside of the security provided by your router.
MSOE provides internet to students as best we can, while not sacrificing the safety or experience of other users. You may not get an Open NAT while on our network for the reasons above, as well as others. This should not impact the speed and quality of your gaming experience, but it may prevent you from hosting in some of your games.
Thank you.

And then reset the MAC address of the XBO: Settings > network > Advanced settings > Alternate mac address > Clear

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 26.16 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Software center not loading
helpdesk-ticket.description: Software center loading bar runs infinitely and does not display programs. Checking in for repair/troubleshooting.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Software center loading bar runs infinitely and does not display programs. Checking in for repair/troubleshooting.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Matt Schladweiler, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11144
There are a few things that this could be. The first step would be to update in Configuration Manager (start and type in those words). Navigate to the actions tab. There will be something in there that says Run Machine Policy Retrieval... click this then click run. This will take up to 20 minutes to run and it runs in the background. You will not be able to see what it is doing. Once this is done, Software center should start working properly.
James Windorff Helpdesk Technician helpdesk@msoe.edu 414 277 7288

Hi Ross Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11150
We have changed the way software is installed on MSOE computers. We now use an application called 'software center' to manage all of the software that is installed through MSOE. helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Payne,
We're doing some testing over here in IT trying to reproduce the problem you are seeing. One thing we know is that devices will try to stay connected to the first connection they make. For example, when we walk from the Great Room back to the IT area, there's an access point in the hall before our offices. We found that the people who had the most problems with connecting were still associated with the access point in the hall, even though there were access points directly above them. We also know that a lot of channel interference on 2.4 ghz radios causes problems when authenticating.
Since we've added more access points in RSOB, the problem appears to have compounded. My guess is that the APs are overlapping each other's areas and causing channel interference. That combined with the stickiness of a device trying to stay connected to the first AP it sees can result in a number of problems. You could be connected to an AP on the first floor when in class on the third.
Here in IT, we turned off the 2.4ghz radios as they are older technology, and all of our devices are equipped with 5.0ghz radios since probably 2012. Next, we reduced the range of the APs so that they are less likely to overlap. When we checked our devices again, they had found the closest AP and connected at 5.0ghz which has many more channels to choose from than 2.4ghz.
I don't want to make that kind of change to RSOB in the middle of the day, but you may be able to force your device to find the closest AP by finding the wireless network on the device (MSOE), deleting it, and re-adding it. I will plan to find time early in the morning or during breaks in class to make changes to the APs in RSOB, and then we'll use that to model other areas with similar problems, like the Library.
We'll try to keep the instructors in RSOB updated.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu
(414) 277-2355

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Urgent request to upgrade Biopac software
helpdesk-ticket.description:
We would like to request that IT process an upgrade to the Biopac software (version BSL4, quote attached) ASAP.
Last week, it came to our attention that MSOE’s current Biopac software (version 3.7, purchased in 2005) is not supported in Windows 10. The software is to be used in a junior-level course, and all juniors now have machines that run Windows 10. I have been working with Michael Timm to determine if version 3.7 might still work on Windows 10. As of yet, we have not gotten the software to communicate with our data acquisition units. The requested software not only supports Windows 10, but it has many new features and modern interface tools. All biomedical engineering and nursing students use this software in courses, and it is also used extensively in summer outreach programs.
Note that Biopac does not offer traditional site licenses. They agreed that the purchase of 12 upgrades would be appropriate, based on our need to run the software concurrently on 12 machines (we have 12 data acquisition units). The software would have to be available for installation from the network.
Rick—Instructors of BE-3900 plan to use this software in week 4. Given the urgency of this upgrade need in order to avoid compromising the ability to meet student learning objectives in the course, Dr. Williams suggested I copy you in this request. Any assistance you can provide in expediting this request will be highly appreciated.
Please contact me if there are any questions.
Thank you for your attention, Jeff LaMack
Jeffrey LaMack, Ph.D. Program Director of Biomedical Engineering Associate Professor, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Department Milwaukee School of Engineering (414) 277-7535

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 26.97 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 26.97 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello Helpdesk,
  Should I be receiving notifications in Jenzabar when I have a PO that needs action on it?  For example, does Jenzabar notify me if “goods need to be received” or an approval request is waiting?
Thanks!

 
Mark Anderson
Director of International Programs & Services
Milwaukee School of Engineering
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202
andersonm@msoe.edu
Ph: +1 414.277.4544

helpdesk-note.body:
Mark,
You should get an email as your req goes through the approval process to become a PO, when a file gets attached, or if changes are made. They can get rather frequent. You will get a notification if you are the next in line to approve a PO. You will get a final notification when the req has become a PO. You will NOT get notification when: you need to send the PO to the vendor, when the invoice has been received and is waiting on a PO, or when the invoice is received for a approved PO and the purchase needs to be marked as received. If it goes too long, or if they are working on a batch of POs, finance may email you. I try to go in a few times a week and just do housekeeping. Jenzabar will have notifications that pop up in the lower right letting you know if you have reqs waiting approval, but mostly you will need to manually go in and mark items as received, etc.
Hope that helps,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu
(414) 277-2355 Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11216

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Dear Helpdesk,
I would like to call ANSYS Mechanical APDL from a command line run so that the program runs in the computers background. It is usually a command line call something like:
[ANSYSPATH] –m 512 –db 1024 –b –p [ANSYSLIC] –I [INPUT_FILE_NAME] –o [OUTPUT_FILE_NAME]
So, something like:
"C:\Program Files\ANSYS Inc\v172\ansys\bin\winx64" –m 512 –db 1024 –b –p ANE3FL –i two_bar_truss.inp –o fem_temp.out
Currently, I cannot get this to work. The call produces an error that reads:
*** IMPORTANT LICENSING MESSAGE ***
ANSYS LICENSE MANAGER ERROR: Failover feature 'ANSYS Multiphysics' specified in license preferences is not available. Request name ane3fl does not exist in the licensing pool. License server system does not support this feature. Feature: ane3fl License path: 1055@applicense2.msoe.edu; FlexNet Licensing error:-18,147 For further information, refer to the FlexNet Licensing documentation, available at "www.flexerasoftware.com". *** ERROR - ANSYS license not available.
I have tried several other variations on the license call, ANE3FL, such as STRUCT or ANSYS. How can I call the correct license for this type of run?
Thanks in advance.
Mike Sracic Mechanical Engineering, S-128 277-2557

I am a graduate student who needs to install follow you printing on my non-msoe computer so that I may utilize printing services on campus. 

How do I install this printing service?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi runnallsk, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11234
If it is a Windows machine: start: run: type \\printers.msoe.edu. There will be a credential box that pops up, you need only use your normal sign in for MSOE services. On the list there will be Follow You Printing (with spaces in it) that appears and you need only double click.
If it is a Mac machine: 1. Navigate to System Preferences -> Print and Scan.
2. Click the + button to add a new printer. 3. Control-Click on the Toolbar and select Customize Toolbar.... Drag the Advanced icon onto the bar, then click the newly added Advanced button 4. Select the Windows device type. 5. Enter a Device URL, There is different syntax based on the os you are working with. This syntax will NOT work with newer versions of OSX. Some versions of Linux and Mac os 10.6.8 are confirmed to work with the below syntax. This may work for everything that defines the printer type as “windows”, and NOT windows spoolss: smb://msoe.edu/username:password@printers.msoe.edu/FollowYouPrinting THIS SETUP RESULTS IN A PRINTER THAT WON’T WORK WHEN USERS CHANGE THEIR DOMAIN PASSWORD AND IT WILL HAVE TO BE REBUILT EACH TIME! 6. In Name field, enter a friendly and informative printer name. 7. Choose a driver for this printer by pulling down the drop-down box and selecting Generic PCL Printer. 8. Click the Add button.
Let us know if this works for you.
James Windorff Helpdesk Technician helpdesk@msoe.edu 414 277 7288

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi Every academic year we have outlook email lists that are created so that we can email the students in our department.
The standard lists that are created are
AE Students AECM students AECV Students CM Students CV Students All AE Majors
Is this being done this year? I was just told by IT that I need to create these lists and submit a ticket. I’m going on my fourth year and I have never been asked to do this. So this is why I’m submitting this question. Also, there are some very old email groups sitting in the global address book.
These lists are very important for getting information to student groups.

helpdesk-ticket.description: Two weeks ago I requested my internet port be changed to T-519 but was informed that the T ports are only telephone ports. There is only one other port and it is T-519-1 and I had been using it and it was working. When the ticket went through for the last request and was processed it (t-519-1) stopped working. I'm wondering if I can get T-519-1 activated again. I looked for the A-0519 and cannot find it in this apartment. Any help would be great, Thanks.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Two weeks ago I requested my internet port be changed to T-519 but was informed that the T ports are only telephone ports. There is only one other port and it is T-519-1 and I had been using it and it was working. When the ticket went through for the last request and was processed it (t-519-1) stopped working. I'm wondering if I can get T-519-1 activated again. I looked for the A-0519 and cannot find it in this apartment. Any help would be great, Thanks.

helpdesk-note.body:
Shana Cook,
Hey Shana, I apologize, I've been very busy troubleshooting the network problems in the Tower, and have not had a moment to have someone make this change to your port. That said, I also did not make any changes to your current working port. Do you have a router or anything like that plugged into the wall port? Is there a MAC address somewhere on the bottom of the device? It would be something along the lines of:
A1:B2:C3:D4:EE:00
six sets of two numbers separated by colons or dashes. If you can provide me with that MAC address, I should be able to see which port you were last connected. I suspect either that port is still working (and I was misinformed about the port numbers) or your device may have been getting a connection from another device. Something like the problem you are experience may help me determine what's causing the issues in the Tower. If you don't have a router between your device and the wall, we'll need to troubleshoot differently.
I'll also attached the email I provided to the Tower building manager. If you can perform the applicable last steps, it would be helpful to the department and to the residents of the Tower.
Link to Tower Update: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/solution/categories/1000010350/folders/1000015760/articles/1000027478-slow-bad-wireless-in-msoe-grohmann-tower-9-8-2016
Thanks,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu
(414) 277-2355

A1:B2:C3:D4:EE:00 

six sets of two numbers separated by colons or dashes. If you can provide me with that MAC address, I should be able to see which port you were last connected. I suspect either that port is still working (and I was misinformed about the port numbers) or your device may have been getting a connection from another device. Something like the problem you are experience may help me determine what's causing the issues in the Tower. If you don't have a router between your device and the wall, we'll need to troubleshoot differently.

I'll also attached the email I provided to the Tower building manager. If you can perform the applicable last steps, it would be helpful to the department and to the residents of the Tower.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 27.41 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 27.41 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-note.body:
removed forwarding from dreyer to morin.
Steps to forward to multiple recipients (looks like 365 does not allow you to forward to multiple email addresses).
In order to create the forwarding: 1. Created a distribution group called foward_to_Morin_and_Dreyer@msoe.edu (added morin and dreyer to this group) 2. In Breese@msoe.edu account, set forwarding on and had it forward to foward_to_Morin_and_Dreyer@msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html:
removed forwarding from dreyer to morin.

Steps to forward to multiple recipients (looks like 365 does not allow you to forward to multiple email addresses).

In order to create the forwarding:
1.  Created a distribution group called foward_to_Morin_and_Dreyer@msoe.edu (added morin and dreyer to this group)
2. In Breese@msoe.edu account, set forwarding on and had it forward to foward_to_Morin_and_Dreyer@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Computer keeps freezing
helpdesk-ticket.description: The laptop I received last week continuously freezes, it mostly happens when the computer heats up a bit and can sometimes happen within a few minutes of booting up. The problem arose since the first day I was able to logon to the laptop which was a day after I picked it up. It is currently running the most recent version of windows 10. I updated most if not all the device drivers and altered some of the power settings to see if it would help and it did help but it hasn’t fixed the problem. I literally just picked up the laptop last Tuesday and having downloaded a few programs both personal and for school use I want to be able to use it without it freezing every single time I’m doing something important. When it freezes all keys and the mouse become unresponsive but the backlight for the keyboard does still turn on and off, the display freezes as well and nothing happens if you wait to see if it responds, the only thing I can do at that point is hold the power button until it turns off and start it up again which deletes any unsaved work that I was working on, has deleted about 3 or 4 of my projects that I had started already in the past week and installing new software is a drag too because if it freezes it will just corrupt the program and I’ll have to delete the files and start all over again which is very time consuming and inconvenient for something that I’m paying for. I was just wondering if this is a problem that has come up more than just a few times already and if you guys have a way to fix it permanently so that it I don’t have to restart the computer manually after doing about half the work on an assignment and having to start almost completely over again.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 12.29 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

How to Fix It
Ask the owner of the group to grant you permission to send to the group, and then try to send a message again. If the group belongs to a different organization than yours, contact the organization's customer service department for assistance. If the group is in your organization and you don't know who the group owner is, you can find it by doing the following in either Outlook on the web or Outlook:
· Open your Sent folder, and then select the original message.
· If you're using Outlook on the web, select the group name located on the To or CC line. If you're using Outlook, double-click the group name on the To or CC line.
· In Outlook on the web, from the pop-up dialog box, choose Owner. In Outlook, choose Contact. The owner's name is listed under Owner.
The owner of the group may have intentionally chosen to restrict who can send messages to it, and they may not want to adjust the existing restriction. In this case, you'll have to contact the group members by some other means, such as sending an email message to their individual email addresses or contacting them by phone.

More Info for Email Admins
Status code: 550 5.7.124
This error occurs when the owner of the distribution group or security group has set up the group to accept messages only from certain addresses. Even a group owner may not be automatically granted permission to send messages to the group.
To fix this issue, the group owner must add the sender's address to the group's allowed senders list. Usually this issue can only be fixed by the group owner.
For more information and steps to fix this issue, see Fix email delivery issues for error code 5.7.124 in Office 365.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 14.13 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 14.13 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
